This chunk is part of a section explaining animated character definitions within the EGG file format, specifically detailing how bundles and tables are used to organize animated values for joints in a skeletal structure.

Bundles may only contain tables; tables may contain more tables, bundles, or any one of the following (<Scalar> entries are optional, and default as shown):

<S$Anim> name {
  <Scalar> fps { 24 }
  <V> { values }
}
